Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.94,0:00:17.72,Thinking,,0,0,0,,Cáo Cāo invaded Yuán Shào, who, in his stress, died.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.14,0:00:23.10,Thinking,NTP,0,0,0,,Before his death, he disinherited his eldest son, Yuán Tán, for his youngest son, Yuán Shàng.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.22,0:00:26.78,Thinking,NTP,0,0,0,,Thus he provoked the struggle between Yuan Tan and Yuan Shang.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.42,0:00:35.65,Thinking,NTP,0,0,0,,Yuan Shang besieged Yuan Tan, compelling him to send Xīn Pí to negotiate his surrender with Cáo Cāo.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.68,0:00:47.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)\i1}Zuǒzhì{\i0}, I'm thinking of returning to aid you,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.44,0:00:53.54,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}but I'm not sure if Yuan Tan's surrender is sincere.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.54,0:00:57.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}It is not sincere.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.82,0:01:02.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}Oh? Then it is deceit?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.63,0:01:04.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}It is no deceit.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.14,0:01:12.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}My lord, you needn't ask his sincerity.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.64,0:01:14.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}You only need to ponder their state.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.19,0:01:19.04,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}Yuan Shao has been losing for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.04,0:01:22.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}His military is exhausted, \Nand his advisers executed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.16,0:01:25.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}His sons quarrel, his state now divided in two.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.24,0:01:28.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}Meanwhile famine and disasters plague the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.16,0:01:33.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}Both the wise and simple know this is \NHeaven itself calling to end the Yuán clan.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.76,0:01:39.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}Now Your Excellency is attacking Jì-Province.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.70,0:01:46.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}If Yuan Shang does not reinforce Jì-Province, then he would lose his base.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.54,0:01:48.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}But if he does reinforce it,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.60,0:01:51.04,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}then Yuan Tan would pursue him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.16,0:01:54.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}With your esteemed might, you should strike his fatigued troops
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.06,0:01:57.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}like a wind sweeping through autumn leaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.25,0:02:02.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}The realm's greatest bane is in Hebei.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.60,0:02:06.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}Pacify Hebei to extend your dominance.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.64,0:02:13.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}And if you please sir... A gift of wine?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.14,0:02:28.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}I regret not meeting you sooner!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.25,0:02:34.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}"The realm's greatest bane is in Hebei."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.56,0:02:38.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}"Pacify Hebei to extend my dominance."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.24,0:02:40.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.32,0:02:45.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}With you as his envoy,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.92,0:02:52.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}even if his surrender is deceit, he will surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.50,0:02:54.98,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(100,358)}Xīn Pí\NStyled: Zuǒzhì
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.70,0:03:33.66,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(120,365)\fade(255,0,255,0,420,1680,1940)}Yuán Tán\NStyled: Xiǎnsī
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.68,0:03:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,This subject, Yuan Tan, \Npays his respects to the Chancellor!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.20,0:03:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are the two generals behind you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.60,0:03:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Lǚ Kuàng and Lǚ Xiáng pay their respects!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.60,0:04:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you two consider each other blood brothers?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.24,0:04:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.52,0:04:10.04,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,I am aware you two were \NYuan Shang's subordinates.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.72,0:04:14.92,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Why are you surrendering now?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.40,0:04:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}Chancellor,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.80,0:04:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}Yuan Shang knows you came to rescue me,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.58,0:04:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}and has fled to Jì-Province.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.58,0:04:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}He ordered those two generals to engage me
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.92,0:04:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}but I had told them on the battlefield,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.66,0:04:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}"When my father was alive, \NI never treated you with disrespect."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.04,0:04:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}"Now why follow my brother and seek my defeat?"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.90,0:04:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}When they heard reason, they submitted.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.25,0:04:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}I again told them,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.37,0:04:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}"Surrender not to me, but to Chancellor Cao."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.45,0:04:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}Thus these two have come
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.45,0:04:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}and await your orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.62,0:05:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}When your father was still alive, \Ndespite all the humiliations,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.10,0:05:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}he never once bowed to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.15,0:05:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}Though you two pity the Yuan clan,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.20,0:05:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}you cannot stand their brothers' conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.42,0:05:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}Now I will name you as marquises!\NYou will accompany my army!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.68,0:05:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Chancellor!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.45,0:05:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Rise!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.33,0:05:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.78,0:05:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I dare ask another question. When do we attack Jì-Province and Yuan Shang?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.40,0:05:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Our supplies are exhausted\N and shipment is treacherous.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.65,0:06:02.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,You can stay at Píngyuán while I set camp at Lìyáng.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.06,0:06:04.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,After we clear the supply lines, we will advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.11,0:06:25.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,You two are now his lackeys.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.02,0:06:27.86,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Why are you still doing here!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.58,0:06:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.82,0:06:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Report!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.08,0:06:42.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Yuan Shang had Yǐn Kǎi guard Máo-fort to maintain supply lines from Shăngdăng!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.76,0:06:44.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,The vanguard has already set up camp!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.67,0:06:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Report!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.26,0:06:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuan Shang had Jǔ Kù hold Hándān-city, \Nleaving Shěn Pèi and Chén Lín to guard Ji-Province!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.73,0:06:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Troops assaulted Pingyuan overnight!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.61,0:06:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems Yuan Shang is really determined to defeat Yuan Tan and I.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.45,0:07:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Report!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.26,0:07:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuan Shang's army is pressing \Ndown on Pingyuan! Yuan Tan pleads great danger!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.52,0:07:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He came so fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.40,0:07:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Gentlemen?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.43,0:07:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Report!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.33,0:07:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Xu You has come back from Xuchang!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.48,0:07:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, Yuan Shang has already sent troops to attack Yuan Tan,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.62,0:07:36.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,yet you still await here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.35,0:07:40.58,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Are you expecting for lightning to smite the two Yuans?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.00,0:07:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all within my plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.00,0:07:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Cao Hong?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.44,0:07:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.42,0:07:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll advance your forces to attack Ji Province.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.38,0:08:01.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,I'll lead an attack to Mao-fort, then Handan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.04,0:08:03.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,We'll meet before the walls of Jì-Province!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.12,0:08:03.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.60,0:08:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Generals, heed my orders!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.92,0:08:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.05,0:08:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare at third watch, we move out at daybreak. \NJi-Province will be ours!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.44,0:08:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.10,0:08:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So there is a lightning...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.62,0:08:19.22,Thinking,,0,0,0,,Cáo Cāo marched his army and crushed Yuan Shang,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.46,0:08:24.34,Thinking,,0,0,0,,who had to send the Overseer of Yù-Province, Yin Kui, \Nto the Cáo Cāo's side to negotiate surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.42,0:08:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.30,0:08:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuan Shang's army is decimated, they've ran 50 li away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.44,0:08:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the Overseer of Yù-Province, Yin Kui is here, under Yuan Shang's orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.30,0:08:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He has come in Yuan Shang's stead to surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.09,0:08:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,First, the elder brother sent someone to surrender
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.23,0:08:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, the little brother sends someone to surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.00,0:09:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender accepted.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.54,0:09:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Zhāng Liáo. Xú Huǎng.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.32,0:09:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.88,0:09:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuan Shang knows I've granted his surrender, he'll be unprepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.35,0:09:18.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,You two will raid their base at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.14,0:09:21.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Leave them not a moment of respite
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.00,0:09:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.50,0:09:27.70,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Whether Yuan Shang is dead or alive,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.00,0:09:32.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,At dawn, I will receive his surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.90,0:09:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.61,0:09:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,"Surreder"?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.80,0:10:17.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Chancellor, we attacked their camp as you wished.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.65,0:10:20.70,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Yuan Shang abandoned all his belongings and fled to Zhōngshān.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.05,0:10:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Let him go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.75,0:10:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Officers!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.50,0:10:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.55,0:10:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We will assault the Jì-Province!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.66,0:10:36.14,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\fade(255,0,255,0,500,1700,2180)}{\pos(588.771,374.066)}Shěn Pèi \NStyled: Zhēngnán
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.10,0:10:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Shěn Pèi!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.38,0:10:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Your lord Yuan Shang has fled to Zhōngshān in defeat!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.52,0:10:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Jì-Province is outmatched, your end is near!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.87,0:10:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not surrender now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.28,0:10:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you await for the waters \Nof Zhang River to flush out your city?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.02,0:11:03.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Uncle, you've been standing here for two days now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.84,0:11:06.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,You should take rest in the tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.14,0:11:14.14,Note (Potential style?),,0,0,0,,Your subject, Yuán Tán, pays \Nhis respects to the Chancellor!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.14,0:11:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}When our former lord reigned, \NHebei was a force to be reckoned with.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.30,0:11:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}Now, our lord has passed,\N and Yuan Tan surrendered
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.30,0:11:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}Yuan Shang was going to save our city.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.00,0:11:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}Yet now he's fleeing to Zhōngshān, \Nbefore even stepping a foot inside the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.53,0:11:45.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Sir, we have seized all eighty of\N Xīn Pí's kinsmen, young and old!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.24,0:11:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}Bring them here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.30,0:11:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.50,0:11:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring them up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.90,0:11:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Move!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.68,0:11:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Move!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.14,0:12:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Move!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.98,0:12:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Ji Province is about to fall! It's only a matter of time, so why not surrender now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.28,0:12:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Please spare us!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.00,0:12:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If everyone in the city remains loyal to Shen Pei, then you will all die!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.12,0:12:18.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,If any of you kills Shen Pei and delivers the city,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.42,0:12:21.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,you'll be a hero for your people, rewarded as such!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.50,0:12:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,After entering the city, \NChancellor Cao will award you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.10,0:12:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Uncle!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.18,0:12:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Please spare us!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.91,0:12:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Please spare us, sire!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.68,0:12:38.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,If any of you that kills Shen Pei and delivers the city,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.92,0:12:41.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,you'll be a hero for your people, rewarded as such!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.22,0:12:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,After entering the city, \NChancellor Cao will award you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.16,0:12:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop shouting!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.89,0:12:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Father! Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.17,0:12:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.90,0:13:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.86,0:13:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,When we enter Jì Province, do not harm any members of the Yuán clan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.20,0:13:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone who surrenders, \Nsoldier or civilian, shall be spared.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.20,0:13:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.24,0:13:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandfather!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.46,0:13:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Uncle!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.65,0:13:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Uncle, if you don't trust me,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.67,0:14:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I can ask Mister Chén to relieve you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.35,0:14:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't possibly keep going on like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.52,0:14:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been three days!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.50,0:14:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Uncle!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.26,0:14:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Uncle!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.76,0:14:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Uncle!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.64,0:15:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody, back!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.10,0:16:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, look! General Xú has captured Shěn Pèi!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.40,0:16:03.94,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\fade(255,0,255,0,500,1700,2180)\pos(597.513,362.626)} Guō Jiā \NStyled: Fèngxiào)
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.35,0:16:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They're coming now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.90,0:16:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,General Xú, please wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.53,0:16:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You pathetic, murdering mongrel! Look where you are now!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.98,0:16:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.60,0:16:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Murderer!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.07,0:16:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Mongrel!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.20,0:16:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Pull him up, bring him to see the Chancellor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.72,0:16:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Look where you are now!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.74,0:16:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Shen Pei.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.18,0:17:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know who opened your gates?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.85,0:17:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It was your nephew, Shěn Róng!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.05,0:17:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,My nephew swore to live and die with the city. Thus, when the city fell,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.32,0:17:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,he was already a step \Nahead of me and died for his nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.54,0:17:25.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,I arrived here yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.83,0:17:29.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Why were there so many archers on the walls?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.55,0:17:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I only regret it was too few!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.50,0:17:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you are loyal to the Yuan clan. You only did what you had to.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.20,0:17:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you surrender now?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.10,0:17:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.31,0:18:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.19,0:18:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,My entire family was murdered by this bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.78,0:18:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if I've flogged him 800 times,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.12,0:18:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,it'd never be enough to quell my hatred! Chancellor!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.16,0:18:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,In life, I serve as Yuán clan's vassal. \NIn death, I will serve as Yuan clan's ghost!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.54,0:18:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not like you lot, hypocrites full of treason and fraud!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.68,0:18:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Come, kill me now!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.22,0:18:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine. I'll respect your wishes. Anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.15,0:18:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord is in the north, and I do not wish to die facing the south!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.11,0:18:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'll bury you north of the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.56,0:18:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Much obliged!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.40,0:18:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}When your elder brother, Xīn Píng, received news that you surrendered,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.02,0:19:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}he died in shame!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.92,0:19:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}He wished on his deathbed, for on the day the city fell,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.12,0:19:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}I would have all eighty of your kin executed!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.64,0:19:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}Now they're with Xīn Píng, just as he wanted!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.30,0:19:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}There are so many loyal men in Hebei.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.04,0:19:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}A pity the Yuan clan could not use them to their fullest.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.62,0:19:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}Had they done so, how could I dare eye this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.25,0:19:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Generals, follow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.00,0:20:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}Isn't that Chén Lín? Chén Kǒngzhāng?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.40,0:20:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}When Yuan Shao was preparing his armies to attack me,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.82,0:20:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}you had composed an Denunciation Essay, \Ncalling for an expedition against me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.44,0:20:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}In it, you had listed my crimes,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.14,0:20:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}but why insult even my father and grandfather!?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.66,0:20:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}The arrow was on the bowstring, I had to shoot it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.82,0:20:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor! Execute him! Execute him!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.67,0:20:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,"An arrow that had to be shot", eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.50,0:20:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring me your essay tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.07,0:20:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You will follow me to Yuan Shao’s tomb, to pay tribute to Běnchū.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.75,0:20:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Forward!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.43,0:21:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Who dares to enter Yuan Mansion
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.77,0:21:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,without my knowledge?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.30,0:21:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,News, Chancellor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.21,0:21:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Your son is inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.30,0:21:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Insolent whelp, why aren't you coming down?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.58,0:21:46.58,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\fade(255,0,255,0,500,1700,2180)\pos(597.513,364.619)}Cáo Pī \NStyled: Zǐhuán)
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.05,0:21:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.40,0:21:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You know of my orders?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.32,0:21:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.70,0:21:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Then why did you defy them?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.28,0:22:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Your son knows its wrong, \Nbut I ask my father to meet someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.00,0:22:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Meet with whom?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.50,0:22:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.11,0:22:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Yuán Xī's wife, Lady Zhēn.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.70,0:22:36.70,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\fade(255,0,255,0,500,1100,1180)\pos(601.457,355.653)}Lady Zhēn
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.69,0:22:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Take good care, do not harm them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.69,0:22:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.96,0:22:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.70,0:22:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Outsiders cannot protect the our house.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.70,0:22:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We are willing to offer Lady Zhen as a wife for your son.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.21,0:23:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,An outsider cannot protect?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.00,0:23:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.01,0:23:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Who do you think you are, to speak thusly?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.15,0:23:14.91,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\fade(255,0,255,0,500,2000,3180)\pos(602.443,353.66)}Lady Liu
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.73,0:23:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you dress like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.17,0:23:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.27,0:23:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Since this is Yuan Běnchū's wife, \Nfine silks and grain will be bestowed
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.28,0:23:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.88,0:23:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.25,0:23:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I have something to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.22,0:23:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.35,0:23:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Please bestow to me... the mercy of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.90,0:24:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Truly, a most fitting wife for my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.06,0:24:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,General Xǔ, you so worked hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.38,0:24:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think any of you'd gotten in the city without me?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.40,0:24:40.90,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\fade(255,0,255,0,420,1900,2220)\pos(120.291,332.74)}Xŭ Chŭ\NStyled: Zhòngkāng
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.00,0:24:42.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,We put our lives at risk\N innumerable times to capture this city!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.44,0:24:43.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Yet you dare to boast!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.18,0:24:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Baseborn ignoramuses, \Nwhat do you have to yap for?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.63,0:25:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, Xǔ Yōu was too impudent, so I had to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.87,0:25:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Ziyuan and I were old friends, and \Nhe humored me often. Why kill him?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.82,0:25:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,General Xǔ.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.18,0:25:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Please bury Ziyuan with full honors.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.02,0:25:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.40,0:25:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}Long ago, Běnchū and I commanded armies together.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.10,0:25:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}Běnchū once asked me:
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.00,0:25:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}If matters go awry, where would you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.00,0:26:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}I asked him, 'Friend, what are you saying?'
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.90,0:26:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}Běnchū said,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.60,0:26:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}To my south cuts a river, \Nto the north blocks lands of Yān and Dài,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.60,0:26:07.72,Note (Potential style?),,0,0,0,,Note: Yān and Dài are ancient names for lands situated in modern-day Hebei and Liaoning.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.16,0:26:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}along with the tribes of the steppes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.28,0:26:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}If I marched south to conquer, would I succeed?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.04,0:26:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}I replied:
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.60,0:26:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}I entrust the wisdom and power of all beneath the heavens,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.86,0:26:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}With virtue on our side, nothing could stop us.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.00,0:26:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}That, I did say before.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.00,0:26:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}Yet now, Běnchū is gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.50,0:26:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}and my lament cannot cease!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.50,0:27:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}The people of Hebei have faced fire and steel. Hence, this year their burden of tax will be cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.66,0:27:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Xu Chu?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.57,0:27:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.58,0:27:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Have the headstones of Ju Shou, Shen Pei, \NXīn Píng, and other gentlemen from Hebei prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.12,0:27:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.31,0:27:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuan Tan, Yuan Shang, \Nand Yuan Xi only cared of killing each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.98,0:27:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,They are sons most unfilial!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.94,0:27:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They may still live, but only barely. \NTheir end will come.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.94,0:27:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Cáo Hóng, place headstones for them as well. \NThey shall be with their father.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.22,0:27:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.56,0:27:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Chen Lin?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.43,0:27:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I am here.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.17,0:27:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Take out that Denunciation Essay you wrote back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.28,0:28:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Read it!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.70,0:28:11.70,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\fade(255,0,255,0,420,4000,4420)\pos(586.154,323.774)}Chén Lín\NStyled: Kǒngzhāng
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.15,0:28:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}{\i1}The Ducal Minister of Works, Cáo Cāo,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.18,0:28:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}his grandfather Cáo Teng,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.20,0:28:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}with the eunuchs, violated the state with depravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.50,0:28:53.50,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}His father, Cáo Song, the eunuch-adopted groveler,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.20,0:28:58.50,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}with his venal false-name, now a briber of the powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.60,0:29:03.40,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}[Cáo] Cāo is heir to the ugly, his obscenity inherent.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.00,0:29:06.66,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}Wicked and vile, loves only to carnage...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.04,0:29:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You...!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.74,0:29:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, please make him stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.84,0:29:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.68,0:29:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}Read it! Why stop it now?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.53,0:29:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}When this essay was spread to Xǔdū,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.53,0:29:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}I suffered migranes and laid ill in bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.83,0:29:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}Reading this text, my senses were opened, my hairs stood on end,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.00,0:29:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}In a cold sweat, my migranes were gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.00,0:29:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}Hence could I lead a grand army \Nto conquer Liyang, to repel Yuan Shao,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.00,0:29:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}and fight him to the last man!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.00,0:29:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}Truly, an essay written like an arrow...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.30,0:29:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}With this arrow loosened,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.90,0:30:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}it made corpses of so many able men on the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.52,0:30:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}their souls now in heaven's bosom.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.10,0:30:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}If I, Cáo Cāo, cannot receive this arrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.40,0:30:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}How could those able men sleep in the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.30,0:30:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}and rest beneath the meadows,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.50,0:30:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}Like stars shining, these words are radiant.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.20,0:30:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}If this text wont be read,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.15,0:30:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}how shall I return this debt of blood to the heavens!?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.95,0:30:39.95,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}A war council setup against tyranny (Dong Zhuo),
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.00,0:30:43.55,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}with drawn swords and beating drums, an order sent out to the East,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.80,0:30:48.40,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}to gather all heroes, and absolve their past sins.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.68,0:30:52.30,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}Thus would there be unity with Cáo Cāo,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.80,0:30:57.30,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}and ally with his ranks. \NWith his skills like hunting-hounds,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.10,0:31:02.30,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}would tooth and nail be used. \NYet [Cáo] Cāo domineers in arrogance.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.70,0:31:06.50,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}Abusing men and their nation, \Npoisoning people and their souls.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.40,0:31:11.60,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}Look through all the annals, \Nof all the consuls most corrupt,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.70,0:31:15.85,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}most glutton and hateful, \Nthere stands [Cáo] Cāo worst of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.20,0:31:19.90,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}Those who bring Cáo Cāo's head,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.99,0:31:24.00,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}will be given lands of five thousand households, and a reward of fifty million!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.00,0:31:28.80,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}Announcing to all in under heaven, let all men know
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.40,0:31:33.90,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,433)}of the calamity that befell our holy dynasty. \NThus saith the law.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.39,0:31:36.58,Thinking,,0,0,0,,After Cáo Cāo conquered Jì-Province,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.99,0:31:39.99,Thinking,,0,0,0,, the Yuan brothers continued to war with each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.60,0:31:44.36,Thinking,,0,0,0,,causing Yuan Shang to flee to Yōu-Province to join with Yuan Xi.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.38,0:31:48.57,Thinking,,0,0,0,,Yuan Tan had surrendered, \Nyet still wished to retake Jì-Province.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.57,0:31:51.82,Thinking,,0,0,0,,Cáo Cāo was furious and began war against Yuan Tan.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.90,0:31:55.26,Thinking,,0,0,0,,Yuan Tan attempted to surrender to Cáo Cāo again, but was refused,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.31,0:31:57.91,Thinking,,0,0,0,,and was finally killed by Cao Hong in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.51,0:32:03.20,Thinking,,0,0,0,,Soon, Cáo Cāo sent his troops north to capture Yōu- and Bìng-Provinces,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.28,0:32:07.25,Thinking,,0,0,0,,then battled the Wuhuan-tribes in the west, in pursuit of Yuan Shang and Yuan Xi
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.52,0:32:11.21,Thinking,,0,0,0,,and fought the final battle to pacify the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.62,0:32:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,- Fèngxiào!  \N- Chancellor!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.02,0:32:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}You had to go through so much just so we could pacify the desert, and now carry on with illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.86,0:32:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}How I can I forgive myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.10,0:32:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}Chancellor... Your grace...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.80,0:32:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}... My life can't repay even a fraction of your grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.10,0:32:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}Fengxiao, in these harsh lands,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.92,0:33:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}if I wanted to return home, how does that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.36,0:33:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}Armies live on swift action.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.16,0:33:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}We travel thousand miles to attack,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.76,0:33:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}but we're lacking in speed due to our heavy supplies.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.84,0:33:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}We should send light troops to move out and cover ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.32,0:33:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}Fengxiao, your words are pertinent.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.10,0:33:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}Then, I will lead veteran troops to advance through the back-road
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.06,0:33:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}Let most of the army to return for further orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.98,0:33:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}Fengxiao.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.30,0:33:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}You should return with them to recover.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.96,0:33:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.26,0:33:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We will meet again soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.90,0:34:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.51,0:34:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.02,0:34:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The desert is hard to pass through. You need a guide.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.01,0:34:46.27,Thinking,,0,0,0,,After Cáo Cāo confronted Yuan Shang and Yuan Xi in Bailang Mountain,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.15,0:34:51.68,Thinking,,0,0,0,,Chief Tàdùn of Wuhuan lead his horsemen on the unwitting enemy force.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.72,0:34:55.28,Thinking,,0,0,0,,In the ensuing onslaught, Tàdùn was killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.49,0:35:00.59,Thinking,,0,0,0,,Yuan Shang and Yuan Xi had to retreat with their few remaining cavalry to Liáodōng.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.26,0:35:05.40,Thinking,,0,0,0,,When Cáo Cāo returned to his lands,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.57,0:35:09.96,Thinking,,0,0,0,,Guo Jia had already passed away, at the age of 38.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.07,0:35:13.57,Thinking,,0,0,0,,His service lasted for eleven years.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.20,0:36:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.88,0:36:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.90,0:36:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor has mourned for so long here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.51,0:36:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We worry for you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.51,0:36:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuan Shang and Yuan Xi have ceded to Liáodōng. It will be hard to reach them.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.68,0:36:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, why not return to the capital of Xǔ[chāng]?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.65,0:36:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,If we stay too long, there's a risk Liú Biǎo in Jīng-Province might grow unruly.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.30,0:36:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Gentlemen, a moment please. This won't take long.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.10,0:36:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We can return once the Yuan brothers' heads have been delivered
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.05,0:37:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.85,0:37:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.49,0:37:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.26,0:37:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Gōngsūn Kāng {\i0}of Liaodong has sent the heads of Yuan Shang and Yuan Xi.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.02,0:37:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What? How...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.27,0:37:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as Fengxiao predicted.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.16,0:37:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,A letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.78,0:37:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}"Yuan Xi and Yuan Shang will flee to Liaodong."
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.76,0:38:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}"Sire should not send troops to follow."
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.24,0:38:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}Gōngsūn Kāng has feared the unity of the Yuan clan, thus will be suspicious of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.08,0:38:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}Were you to use force and haste, they will match it in unity.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.95,0:38:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}But if you stalled,  Gongsun Kang and the Yuans...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.66,0:38:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}They will conspire against one another, as this is their nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.76,0:38:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.10,0:38:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}When I returned, Fengxiao's aide gave this letter to me and said:
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.11,0:38:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}“If Chancellor were to follow the letter..."
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.00,0:38:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}"The matter of Liaodong will be solved."
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.30,0:39:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}We are all veterans with many years behind us.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.18,0:39:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}But Fengxiao was youngest of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.77,0:39:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}He was to be my confidant.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.74,0:39:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}Yet he was taken so soon, I cannot but grieve.
Dialogue: 1,0:39:24.76,0:39:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}Fengxiao is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.13,0:39:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(353.001,443)}O Death, have you seized too soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.46,0:39:53.44,Note (Potential style?),,0,0,0,,{\i1}"Gazing at Dark-Blue Sea" (观沧海) by Cáo Cāo
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.45,0:39:53.91,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord8}East of Jieshi, I gaze at the blue sea.
Dialogue: 1,0:39:55.69,0:40:01.45,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord8} The water dances gently, \NThe mountain island towers.
Dialogue: 1,0:40:02.80,0:40:07.59,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord8}The trees grow thick,\NWhile the grass still lush.
Dialogue: 1,0:40:08.53,0:40:13.43,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord8}Cold autumn winds blow,\NGreat waves surge forth.
Dialogue: 1,0:40:14.87,0:40:18.41,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord8}The path of sun and moon,\Nlike cometh from within.
Dialogue: 1,0:40:18.48,0:40:22.91,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord8}Brilliant band of stars, \NBursting from its depths.
Dialogue: 1,0:40:23.85,0:40:29.95,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord8}Oh, to have such luck!\NI sing, I shout my ambition.
